<P>
JURY AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Judge Slashes $5.74-Million Award Against West Covina Police," 
Metro, July 11: 
</P>
<P>
I will never understand how a judge (one person) can justify in any way 
overruling a jury's (12 people) award. 
</P>
<P>
Why not do away with juries altogether in all cases where the judge does 
whatever he wants? In my opinion this is just a joke and disgrace to our 
so-called judicial system, and a clear violation of our civil rights to have a 
jury of our peers decide on the amounts of awards, etc. 
</P>
