<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOT SO HANDY? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How can one equate advertising with poor quality workmanship or deduce that the 
workmen can't get enough business through referrals? Rubbish! Some of my larger 
jobs have come from advertising in local throwaway newspapers, and it is a tool 
I use for increasing my business. Should consumers avoid all businesses that 
advertise? 
</P>
<P>
Additionally, if a contract is signed by an unlicensed tradesman, the consumer 
has little recourse if the work proves to be shoddy, inadequate or left 
incomplete. Furthermore, contracts must be of a specific form and content, 
including notification of the right to cancel the contract within three 
business days of execution. 
</P>
<P>
JERE ROSENBERG 
</P>
<P>
Hollywood 
</P>
<P>
 Rosenberg is a general contractor. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
