EL MONTE BUSINESS PARK BOUGHT BY LABOR GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Construction Laborer's Pension Trust for Southern California has purchased 
the two-building Airport Business Park, on Santa Anita Avenue in El Monte, for 
$7 million, according to Grubb &amp; Ellis. 
</P>
<P>
The labor group plans to use the entire business park, completed a year ago by 
the Rodine Cos. of Monrovia, for its headquarters, now on Wilshire Boulevard in 
downtown Los Angeles. The move is scheduled for the third quarter of this year. 
</P>
