<TEXT>
<P>
Wells Fargo Bank of Newport Beach has signed a $30-million, long-term lease 
with the Koll Co. of Newport Beach to occupy 71,000 square feet of office space 
at 1940 Main St. in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The bank, which plans to occupy three floors of the 12-story building for its 
Orange County corporate headquarters, is partial owner of the property, 
according to the Newport Beach office of Coldwell Banker Commercial Services, 
which represented Wells Fargo Bank. 
