-- Barbara Zeidman, The city's rent stabilization director ; Photo, A 
LANDLORD'S VIEW -- Steve Melnyk, He is regarded by officials as a model 
low-income landlord ; Photo, Carlos Flores, 6, stands behind broken panes, 
above. Dark hallway, left, is typical of many slum buildings. Union Avenue 
building, below, has been targeted as candidate for "rent escrow" program. J. 
ALBERT DIAZ / Los Angeles Times; Photo, In this Glassell Park aparment 
building, where rooms are small and overcrowded, children often prefer to 
congregate in the more spacious hallway to ride their bikes or toss a baseball. 
IRIS SCHNEIDER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
