<P>
BAHRAIN FOREIGN MINISTER LEAVES FOR U.S. TALKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bahrain's Foreign Minister Sheik Mohammed ibn Mubarak Khalifa left Friday for 
the United States for talks on regional issues. 
</P>
<P>
The Gulf news agency, received in Nicosia, said during his four-day visit 
Mohammed will deliver a message to President Bush from Bahrain's Emir Sheik Isa 
ibn Salman al Khalifa. 
</P>
