<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOUSE, 80, CHARGED IN CRUTCH BEATING DEATH OF HUSBAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TRIKALA, Greece 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 80-year-old woman who allegedly beat her husband with a crutch during an 
argument over their will has been charged with his death, police say. 
</P>
<P>
Stavroula Plexidas was arrested Wednesday in Megalochori, a small farming 
village on this outskirts of this town in central Greece, and charged with the 
murder of her husband, Nikolaos, 78. 
</P>
<P>
Plexidas was arrested after her dying husband told police that she had beaten 
him with her wooden crutch as he lay in bed Tuesday night after an argument 
over their estate, a police spokesman said Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
