<P>
LIKE FATHER, LIKE SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding "How Fathers Figure," by Paul Ciotti: If one were stupid enough to 
rely on the documented findings of the male psychologists and physicians Ciotti 
refers to, one would conclude that boys raised by their mothers are unfriendly, 
immature, disobedient, cowardly, intellectually deficient and suffer low 
self-esteem. Because Ciotti can't come up with anything deep about fatherhood, 
he resorts to mother-bashing. 
</P>
<P>
Shame on you. 
</P>
<P>
BLAKE LATIMER 
</P>
<P>
Venice 
