<P>
DANNEMEYER ON HOMOSEXUALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Well, another flap and more oppression as Rep. William E. Dannemeyer 
(R-Fullerton) is at it again: Rather than striving for progress, growth, and 
social relevance, he continues to incite and feed the flames of racism and 
widespread prejudice against "the homosexual movement." 
</P>
<P>
I think Dannemeyer's tactics are despicable and contemptuous of the system of 
democracy that he infests. Dannemeyer is really out on a limb, however, this 
time. 
</P>
<P>
Dannemeyer has no business airing that kind of discussion in our Congressional 
Record. We don't have straight congressmen describing heterosexual sex for the 
sake of straw issues. There is no reason to further cloud and bias the issues 
by Dannemeyer's feeding into ignorance in such a forum and in such a 
self-serving and self-righteous manner. 
</P>
<P>
I am outraged at Dannemeyer's actions because he continues to abuse and tax the 
ideals of Democracy with his perverted and twisted ideas of what constitute 
morality, fairness and human compassion. 
</P>
<P>
I strongly support the legislative efforts of my progressive and clear-thinking 
elected officials in their affirmative efforts to pass the legislation to 
guarantee my fellow gay men and women the same anti-discriminatory protections 
afforded racial minorities in the 1964 Civil Rights Act. 
</P>
<P>
ANTHONY RAMIREZ 
</P>
