<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAMS SIGN TONY SLATON TO ONE-YEAR CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rams got another offensive lineman into camp Saturday when reserve 
center-guard Tony Slaton agreed to a one-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
Slaton's signing eased a major concern for Ram Coach John Robinson, who 
appeared headed into the exhibition season with a makeshift offensive line. But 
the signing of Slaton and left tackle Irv Pankey this weekend gives the Rams 
three starters and a top backup in Slaton. 
</P>
<P>
To make room for Pankey, the team released Thor Salanoa, a linebacker from BYU. 
They must make room for Slaton today. 
</P>
