<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GILBERT RALLIES TO WIN, PLAYS MAYOTTE FOR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Tim Mayotte, yielding only 10 points on his serve, advanced to the 
final of the Sovran Bank tournament Saturday in Washington with a 6-3, 6-2 
victory over Todd Witsken. 
</P>
<P>
Mayotte blasted five aces and never faced a break point in eliminating Witsken 
in 71 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal, Brad Gilbert rallied from 0-2 in the final set for a 
6-4, 3-6, 6-3 win over Richey Reneberg. 
</P>
<P>
Martin Jaite of Argentina defeated Jens Woehrmann of West Germany, 5-7, 6-4, 
6-3, to advance to the final of a Grand Prix tournament at Stuttgart, West 
Germany. 
</P>
<P>
Jaite will play Goran Prpic of Yugoslavia, who beat Sergio Bruguera of Spain, 
3-6, 7-5, 6-1, in the other semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Katerina Maleeva of Bulgaria and unseeded qualifier Sabine Hack of 
West Germany reached the final of the Volvo Ladies International in Bastad, 
Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
Maleeva, ranked 15th in the world, battled for almost 2 hours before beating 
fourth-seeded Sandra Cecchini of Italy, 6-4, 2-6, 6-4. Hack defeated Sweden's 
Maria Strandlund, 6-2, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
This is the first major final for the 19-year-old Hack, who is ranked 105th in 
the world. 
</P>
<P>
John McEnroe will be missing because of a shoulder strain Monday when play 
begins in the Volvo International at Stratton Mountain, Vt. 
</P>
<P>
Boris Becker, the recent winner at Wimbledon, withdrew earlier because of a leg 
muscle strain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
