<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCANDALIZED BY 'SCANDAL' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Travel Section is my favorite reading of the week. Doublefold then was my 
shock and disgust at the tasteless article by Andrew Marton, "A Scandalous Tour 
of Washington" (July 16). Has the Travel Section stooped to trash and scandal 
techniques as TV and yellow journalism (have)? I hope not. The article has no 
place in (the) wholesome, intellectual, if you will, pursuit of normal American 
entertainment. We look to the Travel Section for enjoyment and helpful tips on 
places to go, what to see. Not this trash. 
</P>
<P>
I hope that Jerry Hulse, Judith Morgan, Peter Greenberg and (Bob) O'Sullivan 
will continue their valuable contributions to our enjoyment and that you will 
leave the above to the scandal rags. 
</P>
<P>
VIRGINIA MACKOOL 
</P>
<P>
Arcadia 
</P>
</TEXT>
